Files:
- e2e/security.e2e.ts (move ws.close() into finally block)

Context:
The test `concurrent setToolPermission calls with WebSocket` (around line 670 in security.e2e.ts) creates a raw WebSocket:
```ts
const { wsUrl, wsSecret } = await fetchWsInfo(server.port, server.secret);
const ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl, [...]);
```
At the end of the test body:
```ts
      ws.close();        // <-- line ~773, outside finally
    } finally {
      await server.kill();
      cleanupTestConfigDir(configDir);
    }
```
The fix is:
```ts
    } finally {
      ws.close();        // <-- moved here
      await server.kill();
      cleanupTestConfigDir(configDir);
    }
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change anything else in the test logic
- `ws.close()` should be the FIRST statement in the finally block so it runs before the server is killed (closing the WS client before the server is cleaner)

Files:
- e2e/strict-csp.e2e.ts (add try/finally with connect-src reset for the connect-src:'none' test)

Context:
Locate the test that calls `set-connect-src` with `connectSrcNone: true`. The pattern to fix:
```ts
await strictCspServer.control('set-connect-src', { connectSrcNone: true });

const page = await openTestAppTab(extensionContext, strictCspServer.url, mcpServer);
// ... assertions ...
await page.close();
// no reset!
```
The fix:
```ts
await strictCspServer.control('set-connect-src', { connectSrcNone: true });
try {
  const page = await openTestAppTab(extensionContext, strictCspServer.url, mcpServer);
  try {
    // ... assertions ...
  } finally {
    await page.close();
  }
} finally {
  await strictCspServer.control('set-connect-src', { connectSrcNone: false }).catch(() => {});
}
```
Note: `.catch(() => {})` is a best-effort since the test server might be in a bad state.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the test's assertions
- Only add the cleanup guarantee

Files:
- e2e/side-panel-open-tab.e2e.ts (fix homepageServer port and close)

Context:
The test creates an http.Server and listens on port 9876:
```ts
homepageServer.listen(9876, resolve);  // hardcoded port
```
With an EADDRINUSE fallback:
```ts
homepageServer.once('error', (err) => {
  if (err.code === 'EADDRINUSE') {
    homepageServer.listen(0, resolve);  // fallback to random port
  }
});
```
But then the URL assertion uses the hardcoded port:
```ts
expect(newPage.url()).toContain('localhost:9876');
```
And cleanup:
```ts
homepageServer.close();  // fire and forget
```

Fix:
1. Always use port 0 (dynamic) from the start:
```ts
homepageServer.listen(0, () => {
  const homepagePort = (homepageServer.address() as net.AddressInfo).port;
  resolve();
});
```
2. Store the actual port and use it in the URL assertion:
```ts
expect(newPage.url()).toContain(`localhost:${String(homepagePort)}`);
```
3. Wrap close() in a Promise:
```ts
await new Promise<void>(resolve => homepageServer.close(() => resolve()));
```

The test needs to import `import net from 'node:net'` if not already imported, or read the port via `(homepageServer.address() as net.AddressInfo).port`.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the test's assertion about the page URL behavior — just fix what port it checks
- The server still needs to serve the same 'homepage-test' content at the root path

Files:
- e2e/stress-mcp-dispatch.e2e.ts (wrap all 4 test page handles in try/finally)
- e2e/progress.e2e.ts (move setSlow(0) into finally block)

Context for stress-mcp-dispatch.e2e.ts:
All four tests follow this pattern:
```ts
const page = await setupToolTest(mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient);
// ... assertions ...
await page.close();
```
Fix pattern:
```ts
const page = await setupToolTest(mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient);
try {
  // ... assertions ...
} finally {
  await page.close();
}
```
The third test ('slow tool — tab closes during execution') also opens a second page:
```ts
const newPage = await openTestAppTab(extensionContext, testServer.url, mcpServer, testServer);
// ...
await newPage.close();
```
This second page also needs a try/finally.

Context for progress.e2e.ts:
The timeout test currently:
```ts
await testServer.setSlow(35_000);
// ... assertions that can throw ...
await testServer.setSlow(0);
await page.close();
```
Fix:
```ts
await testServer.setSlow(35_000);
try {
  // ... assertions ...
} finally {
  await testServer.setSlow(0).catch(() => {});
  await page.close().catch(() => {});
}
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change any test assertions
- Do NOT wrap the entire test body in try/finally if the page comes from a fixture — only wrap the user-created pages
- In stress-mcp-dispatch.e2e.ts, the `page` from `setupToolTest` is the main tab page — wrap it; `newPage` from `openTestAppTab` is the recovery page — also wrap it
